    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Replicate records between tools with HubSpot and Google Sheets 24/7\n\n**Pattern:** Two-System Sync · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nReplicate records between tools with HubSpot and Google Sheets 24/7. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual contact sync is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWeekly Schedule → Pull Side A (HubSpot) → Diff the Two Systems → Create Missing in Google Sheets → Gather Sync Results → Tag Pipeline Metadata → Sort Contacts Newest First → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to two-system sync without manual effort\n- Anyone automating contact sync in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Discord webhook URL; Google OAuth2 / service account; HubSpot private-app token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
